2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper focuses on wireless communication networks and their performance, which falls under the scope of networking and internet architecture. 
3. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper discusses a decentralized link activation strategy, which is a common topic in social and information networks. 
4. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - The paper proposes a modified link activation strategy that is based on random graph theory, which is a common topic in distributed computing. 
5. cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) - The paper discusses a decentralized link activation strategy, which is a common topic in multiagent systems.
